usdBridgeEthernetMIB.name: usdBridgeEthernetMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

usdBridgeEthernetMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdBridgeEthernetMIB.description: The Bridge Ethernet MIB for the Unisphere Networks Inc. enterprise.

usdBridgedEthernetNextIfIndex.name: usdBridgedEthernetNextIfIndex
usdBridgedEthernetNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdBridgedEthernetIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdBridgedEthernetIfTable.name: usdBridgedEthernetIfTable
usdBridgedEthernetIfTable.description: The parameters for the BridgedEthernet service on this interface.

usdBridgedEthernetIfEntry.name: usdBridgedEthernetIfEntry
usdBridgedEthernetIfEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular Bridged Ethernet interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable

usdBridgedEthernetIfIfIndex.name: usdBridgedEthernetIfIfIndex
usdBridgedEthernetIfIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEntry.

usdBridgedEthernetProxyArp.name: usdBridgedEthernetProxyArp
usdBridgedEthernetProxyArp.description: The proxyArp configuration setting for this entry. *** NOTE: This MIB object has been obsoleted. ***

usdBridgedEthernetIfLowerIfIndex.name: usdBridgedEthernetIfLowerIfIndex
usdBridgedEthernetIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this Bridged Ethernet interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdBridgedEthernetIfRowStatus.name: usdBridgedEthernetIfRowStatus
usdBridgedEthernetIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdBridgedEthernetIfRowStatus usdBridgedEthernetIfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdBridgedEthernetIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdBridgedEthernetNextIfIndex. The interface identified by usdBridgedEthernetIfLowerIfIndex must exist, and must be an interface type that permits layering of Bridged Ethernet above it. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdBridgedEthernetCompliance.name: usdBridgedEthernetCompliance
usdBridgedEthernetCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere bridged Ethernet MIB.

usdBridgedEthernetGroup.name: usdBridgedEthernetGroup
usdBridgedEthernetGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of Bridged Ethernet interfaces in a Unisphere product. This group became obsolete when usdBridgedEthernetProxyArp was made obsolete.

usdBridgedEthernetGroup2.name: usdBridgedEthernetGroup2
usdBridgedEthernetGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of Bridged Ethernet interfaces in a Unisphere product.
